Phase 5: Remaining Section 2 workflow gaps - field additions, new models & business logic

Models updated (46 new columns across 4 tables):
- asset.py: AR-1 lifecycle_state, AR-2 parent_asset/functional_location,
  AR-3 criticality/risk_score, AR-5 warranty fields, AR-6 nameplate/specs,
  AR-7 depreciation fields (19 columns)
- incident.py: IN-4 incident_subtype, IN-5 OSHA/regulatory fields,
  IN-1 failure_analysis link (5 columns)
- work_order.py: WO-2 job_plan, WO-3 scheduled/actual dates,
  WO-4 approval fields, WO-5 cost rollup columns, WO-8 safety/LOTO,
  WO-9 feedback fields, WO-10 follow-up/parent WO (19 columns)
- maintenance_request.py: MR-2 SLA fields, MR-6 request_category (5 columns)

New models created:
- VendorInvoice + VendorInvoiceLine (MW-17: 3-way matching)
- ToolCheckout (MW-14: tool/equipment checkout tracking)

New business logic:
- MR-1: Priority auto-calculation from asset criticality x severity
- MR-4: Duplicate MR detection for same asset
- PO-1: 3-way matching service (PO vs GR vs Invoice)
- WO-10: Follow-up WO server action
- Vendor invoice workflow hook

Entity JSON updates: asset, incident, work_order, maintenance_request
